1
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:22,370
You’re Ranya, right?

2
00:00:22,980 --> 00:00:23,600
Yeah.

3
00:00:29,300 --> 00:00:31,156
Give us a pretty smile.

4
00:00:31,214 --> 00:00:32,501
You’re about to be famous, after all.

5
00:00:33,120 --> 00:00:34,290
Come on, smile!

6
00:00:36,930 --> 00:00:38,930
You’re just a maid’s niece,

7
00:00:39,190 --> 00:00:42,734
but you’ve forgotten your place enough to attend school with your masters.

8
00:00:43,110 --> 00:00:46,247
If you’re not a parasite, then what is?

9
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:50,800
How did you know?

10
00:00:51,140 --> 00:00:52,349
Well, am I wrong?

11
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:57,003
Or has our school sunk so low that they just let any trash in now?

12
00:00:58,270 --> 00:01:01,454
Or wait... maybe you used 'other' methods.

13
00:01:01,930 --> 00:01:03,672
Like...

14
00:01:05,880 --> 00:01:07,025
selling your body?

15
00:01:10,770 --> 00:01:12,509
Don't you dare think you can just say whatever the hell you want!

16
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:20,814
What the...?

17
00:01:21,520 --> 00:01:22,545
Guys, I’ve got something to show off.

18
00:01:34,550 --> 00:01:35,956
Give us a pretty smile.

19
00:01:36,320 --> 00:01:37,520
You’re about to be famous, after all.

20
00:01:37,890 --> 00:01:40,574
as I told you I’d handle it.

21
00:01:40,603 --> 00:01:42,174
Holy shit!!

22
00:01:49,530 --> 00:01:50,101
Hey!!

23
00:01:54,100 --> 00:01:55,120
Ranya!

24
00:01:57,767 --> 00:01:58,632
Ranya!

25
00:01:58,654 --> 00:01:59,141
Stop!

26
00:01:59,141 --> 00:02:00,800
You stop! Let me go!

27
00:02:07,050 --> 00:02:07,912
Enough.

28
00:02:09,380 --> 00:02:11,825
If the teacher sees us, we’re all going to get in trouble.

29
00:02:12,123 --> 00:02:14,120
You really think I’m gonna get in trouble?

30
00:02:14,480 --> 00:02:16,276
Don’t you know who my parents are?

31
00:02:16,950 --> 00:02:21,527
Living with those elitists turned you into a stuck-up brat like Pimchat,Huh?!

32
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:24,120
Hey! Watch your mouth. What if P’Tina hears you?

33
00:02:24,145 --> 00:02:25,789
Why do you even care?

34
00:02:26,720 --> 00:02:29,032
I’ve hated those two for a long time.

35
00:02:29,790 --> 00:02:33,643
Just because they’re a little rich, they think they can look down on everyone.

36
00:02:34,130 --> 00:02:35,476
It makes me sick.

37
00:02:35,830 --> 00:02:38,494
Oh, wait I bet you’ve been on the receiving end too.

38
00:02:39,470 --> 00:02:42,421
Makes sense, though. When you’re living off their charity,

39
00:02:43,080 --> 00:02:45,381
you just have to sit there and let Chat boss you around like a dog.

40
00:02:45,418 --> 00:02:47,047
You can say whatever you want about me,

41
00:02:47,990 --> 00:02:49,120
but don't you dare talk about P’Chat.

42
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:52,109
How long are you going to keep playing the "good person," huh?

43
00:02:52,810 --> 00:02:56,472
I know for a fact that Chat doesn't even like your face.

44
00:02:58,470 --> 00:02:59,920
Whether she likes me or not,

45
00:03:02,230 --> 00:03:03,840
I owe her family everything.

46
00:03:05,700 --> 00:03:07,592
I might be an orphan,

47
00:03:10,763 --> 00:03:12,872
but I was raised to know the value of gratitude.

48
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:20,967
If having parents meant being raised to act like you guys,

49
00:03:23,185 --> 00:03:24,560
I’d rather be an orphan.

50
00:03:24,940 --> 00:03:26,109
Ranya!!

51
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:31,098
Thank you, Sis.

52
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:38,676
Your face...

53
00:04:39,260 --> 00:04:39,912
Yes?

54
00:04:42,410 --> 00:04:43,738
The first-aid kit is in the kitchen.

55
00:04:52,470 --> 00:04:54,734
Oh! What are you doing?!

56
00:04:54,890 --> 00:04:56,072
You’re hurt too.

57
00:04:58,500 --> 00:04:59,789
Do you want to tend to our wounds together?

58
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:05,672
Why you...! Are you trying to get back at me?

59
00:05:05,709 --> 00:05:06,996
Not at all.

60
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:10,850
Look at that face... you’re quite playful.

61
00:05:11,370 --> 00:05:13,461
My Grandma taught me to stand my ground.

62
00:05:13,890 --> 00:05:15,890
If people are nice to me, I’m nice back.

63
00:05:18,540 --> 00:05:20,043
Well, I am being nice to you.

64
00:05:21,950 --> 00:05:23,141
To be honest?

65
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:26,087
I’m still a little mad at you.

66
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:31,469
But since you got hurt helping me out,

67
00:05:32,790 --> 00:05:33,927
let's just call it even.

68
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:36,756
Oh, really?

69
00:05:38,150 --> 00:05:40,996
We're even? Just like that?

70
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:42,458
Hey! Stop tickling me!

71
00:06:06,792 --> 00:06:08,460
Auntie! Help me!

72
00:06:08,501 --> 00:06:09,112
Mom!

73
00:06:11,580 --> 00:06:13,352
Look at what Ranya's doing!

74
00:06:29,287 --> 00:06:31,600
How could you tell? And what about yours?

75
00:06:33,220 --> 00:06:34,341
Come on, let me see.

76
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:38,807
Let’s trade.

77
00:06:39,960 --> 00:06:42,661
No way. I’m not letting you see.

78
00:09:12,850 --> 00:09:14,981
Ran, do you think Mom was happy?

79
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:20,327
Why would you say something like that, P’Chat?

80
00:09:23,250 --> 00:09:24,887
Ever since I was born,

81
00:09:27,790 --> 00:09:30,254
all I’ve ever seen is Mom being sick like this.

82
00:09:34,960 --> 00:09:45,541
My relatives always like to say that the reason she’s like this is because she gave birth to me.

83
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:55,236
If I hadn’t been born,

84
00:09:56,890 --> 00:09:58,458
Mom would probably still be here, right?

85
00:10:03,240 --> 00:10:04,741
Don’t, P’Chat.

86
00:10:08,070 --> 00:10:09,592
Don’t talk like that.

87
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:20,770
If I hadn’t been born, Mom wouldn’t have had to die like this.

88
00:10:20,821 --> 00:10:21,701
P’Chat...

89
00:10:27,020 --> 00:10:33,207
do you really think Auntie hasn’t been happy at all all this time?

90
00:10:38,130 --> 00:10:40,087
Ever since I moved in here,

91
00:10:43,980 --> 00:10:46,567
I’ve seen her smile every single day

92
00:10:49,270 --> 00:10:50,756
every time she was with you.
